{"questionId":"35036190","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Haruka has an eco-friendly bag in the shape of a cuboid with width 12 cm, length 36 cm and height of 9 cm. The bag is made from five rectangular pieces of cloth and is open at the top.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/fa2cde648e283f77cbb36aa5c212d2a0270dba26.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Nanako decides to make her own eco-friendly bag in the shape of a cuboid such that the surface area is minimized.</p>\n<p>The width of Nanako’s bag is <em>x </em>cm, its length is three times its width and its height is <em>y </em>cm.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/d81b773675ca9129daf531a4f9b95522a7f26026.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">The volume of Nanako’s bag is 3888 cm<sup>3</sup>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Use your answers to parts (c) and (d) to show that</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"A = 3{x^2} + \\frac{{10368}}{x}\">\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>10368</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"A = 3{x^2} + 8x\\left( {\\frac{{1296}}{{{x^2}}}} \\right)\">\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>8</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>1296</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mi>x</mi>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em><strong>(ft)</strong><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>Award <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em><strong>(ft)</strong> for correct rearrangement of their part (c) seen (rearrangement may be seen in part(c)), award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for substitution of their part (c) into their part (d) but only if this leads to the given answer, which must be shown.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"A = 3{x^2} + \\frac{{10368}}{x}\">\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>10368</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(AG)</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"35036190","referenceCode":"18N.2.SL.TZ0.T_6e","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Use your answers to parts (c) and (d) to show that A = 3 x 2 + 10368 x .","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.1—Introduction of differential calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.3—Differentiating polynomials, n E Z","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.6—Stationary points, local max and min","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.7—Optimisation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}